Interface Command

All Known Implementing Classes:
DeleteCommand, DownloadCommand, ListFilesCommand, LoginCommand, LogoutCommand, RegisterCommand, UploadCommand
public interface Command
Command is an interface that defines the structure for all command classes. Each command must implement methods for execution and parameter initialization.

    Method
    Description

  • Method Details

    • execute

      void execute(FileClient fileClient, AuthClient authClient)
      Executes the command. This method contains the logic for performing the specific operation of the command.
      Parameters:
      fileClient - The FileClient instance for file-related operations.
      authClient - The AuthClient instance for authentication operations.

    • setEverything

      void setEverything(List<String> parameters, SessionContext sessionContext, SessionManager sessionManager)
      Sets the necessary context and parameters for the command. This method initializes the command with the required input parameters and session context.
      Parameters:
      parameters - The list of input parameters for the command.
      sessionContext - The session context for the current user.
      sessionManager - The session manager for managing session data.
